phrases: Yes, something between a Corpse and a human.
You are... the same as me, then?
Either way, it means you are not human!
If you are saying you are my enemy...
Corpse s are the enemy of humanity.
That does not mean we can have the Corpses accompany us!
I will turn everyone here into Corpse s.
You are a Corpseless, not a Corpse.
Your body may be a Corpse, but your mind's still human.
This Iron Fortress goes to Daimond Citadel, does not it?
It does according to its schedule.
It is the Warlord's greatest stronghold.
Ayame-sama, if we are heading to Daimond Citadel
If you do, we promise we will stay in this car.
Hey, I am trying to talk
Although I am not leaving this train whether you agree to it or not.
Are you human or a Corpse?!
I have to look at it from the side.
Do not just open the window!
We will be back this evening with more food.
Like this is going to be enough.
And this is for your unborn baby.
There is not enough food and water for the number of people that are onboard.
Are we going to make it?
It is the last safe place we can go to.
But what if Daimond Citadel does not take us in?
The current elder is Ayame-sama's uncle.
We will not be turned away.
You have oil all over your hands!
Your body's healed, has not it?
It is because your body is a Corpse's.
You should be able to move around fine now.
You said you were going to Daimond Citadel.
I cannot tell you what, but I am on an important mission.
Are you interested in Daimond Citadel too?
They are at the forefront of Corpses research.
They might be able to do something... about this Corpseless condition.
Did not you want to get off?
It is not that I fully believe... your Corpseless story.
But... if I am trapped inside this boiler car for three days...
You will ride the Iron Fortress with me.
And you will be my shield.
When I fight for too long, I fall asleep.
That is why I need a living shield.
It is not like you have to worry about getting bit by a Corpse, right?
You are going to Daimond Citadel, right?
You are not much of a shield right now!
How could you let the Corpse onto the train?
It is still not too late.
We should throw the Corpses off!
They promised they would remain in the rear car.
Like a Corpse knows how to keep a promise?!
Do the Six Chiefs not have any sense of gratitude?
And that man has tried to do the right thing even before becoming a Corpse.
Y-You cannot just barge in here!
They demand we stop the Iron Fortress.
We want to hold a funeral.
We want to pray for our family.
Our prayers will not reach them if we go too far.
Do you want our grandchildren unable to pass on?!
You are hopeless, how many times do I have to tell you?
You spin around and boom, boom, bam.
Ju Just because you can do it...
You are already getting overpowered when I have not even removed my restraint.
What is that thing around your neck for?
It is just that if I remove mine, I can fight at my full potential.
But after a while, the curse spreads and I get tired.
She is not supposed to come out!
You promised you were going to stay in the boiler car.
You are just like the Corpse.
I knew not to trust you.
I am taking Nameless back with me right now.
I will make sure she cooperates until we reach Daimond Citadel!
You think you can make me?
What is the meaning of this?
You would not understand even if I told you.
We never should have let Corpse s onboard!
Let us remove them from the train now.
I would like to see you try.
I have got bad news, Captain.
Seems like the water tank we patched together is busted.
No way it is making it to the next station.
Check and see if the pressure's rising.
There are no Corpse s in sight.
How long do we need in order to repair the water tank?
We might be done by morning.
We can have the lookouts rotate in shifts.
Then let us hold a vigil since the Iron Fortress is stopped.
I would like to pray as well.
It is not like praying is going to bring them back to life.
Were you particularly close with your teacher?
That is just the kind of man I am.
You are not going to pray?
I lost my family years ago.
It is a pretty common story.
Losing your family to the Corpses.
What is that in your right hand?
It hurts when I get hit by it.
Just a rock you can find around any river.
I found two of these pretty rocks with my sister.
I told her she could have both...
I never planned on keeping it as a memento.
And my sister was caught by the Corpse.
It is a pretty common story, is not it?
But what do you think her stupid brother did?
I made an excuse about calling for help...
I tried to rely on someone else.
The cowardly brother cried and apologized.
But it was already too late.
Even if it meant dying with her...
No matter how much I hate myself for running away...
Yeah, that is a pretty common story.
What are you planning on doing?
What if they attack us first?
Please allow us to do this, Ayame-sama!
If you want war, I am happy to oblige!
Stop trying to act brave when you are weak.
They are the ones doing the provoking.
I knew the Corpseless were our enemy!
We have to protect our families!
It is dangerous, please come down.
Mother... will not be able to have you.
I did not come to fight.
Hey, can you do me a favor?
Do you need to go potty?
As the one left in charge of the Iron Fortress...
Why are not you using your right arm?!
Why do not you just grab and bite me?!
I will not run away anymore.
Even if it would save me.
I am not sacrificing any more lives!
It is the Corpses who are our enemy.
Those who still believe he is our enemy...
I shall give you the opportunity to check for yourself.
I am sorry for testing you like that.
But why did you take the blade directly?
You could have grabbed my arm.
It has not been long since I became like this, so...
You do not need to be so concerned.
All that laughing made me hungry.
I will get you a bowl.
But I do not need that.
The stuff that comes out when you cut someone.
It must be because of your bleeding.
Are you telling us to become Corpse too?!
She is just a monster after all!
It is not my fault, I got hungry.
When I cannot see anything ahead
And slam everything onto the ground
My soul is devoted to my friend
That connect you make a sound
There are just dreams in the same rain
I am tired of getting answers
The ideal only has its doors
City is uplifted and drown in noise
I will still sing and stop turning the rudder
